cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper deals with issues related to online privacy, data collection, and accuracy of user profiles. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society) which deals with the social and ethical aspects of computing. The paper also discusses concerns related to data security and accuracy, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of online surveys and in-person interviews to analyze user concerns and profile accuracy could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper discusses the implications for public policy management, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
